sentences.english: The club offers lessons in Irish dance and clogging.
sentences.chinese: 這傢俱樂部有踢踏舞和木屐舞課程。

sentences.english: But let us look at the process of klomps production.
sentences.chinese: 看一下木屐鞋的生產過程。

sentences.english: But during the summer, maiko will wear black lacquered Okobo.
sentences.chinese: 不過夏天時，舞妓會穿着上了黑漆的高跟木屐。

sentences.english: Okobo are made of one piece of solid wood forming the sole.
sentences.chinese: 高跟木屐鞋底是用一塊結實的木頭做成。

sentences.english: He pulled clogs , a green military uniform worn down to the anterior .
sentences.chinese: 他拖着木屐，一件破舊的綠軍服垂到膝前。

sentences.english: The first thing to see is an exposition of historic klomps.
sentences.chinese: 首先看到的是傳統木屐鞋的介紹。

sentences.english: Clogs are very famous; I think they are special souvenir.
sentences.chinese: 木屐是非常有名的，我認爲他們是特殊的紀念品。

sentences.english: we talked about she has the kimono, she has the geta shoes.
sentences.chinese: 接着我們討論了，她穿着和服和木屐。

sentences.english: I want to know if your umbrella is on the right or left side of the clogs.
sentences.chinese: 您的傘是放在木屐左邊了呢還是右邊？

sentences.english: Here you may buy klomps of all colors and sizes.
sentences.chinese: 在這裏你可以買到各種顏色和款式的木屐鞋。
